-- Gilts Fall as Pound Rises After Employment Report, BOE Minutes
-- B y   M o r g a n e   L a p e y r e   a n d   L u k a n y o   M n y a n d a
-- 2013-08-14T08:56:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-14/gilts-fall-as-pound-rises-after-employment-report-boe-minutes.html
U.K. 10-year bonds declined for a
third day after a report showed jobless claims dropped more in
July than economists forecast, adding to signs Britain’s economy
is recovering.  The benchmark yield increased to the highest since October
2011 even as a separate report showed the  unemployment rate 
remained at 7.8 percent in the second quarter.  Bank of England 
minutes showed Governor  Mark Carney  failed to unite policy
makers on implementing forward guidance with  Martin Weale 
favoring a tougher inflation stance. The pound rose against the
dollar and the euro.  The 10-year gilt yield rose two basis points, or 0.02
percentage point, to 2.62 percent at 9:50 a.m. London time after
climbing to 2.64 percent, the highest since Oct. 28, 2011. The
1.75 percent bond due in September 2022 fell 0.15, or 1.50
pounds per 1,000-pound ($1,548) face amount, to 93.045.  The pound gained 0.2 percent to 85.70 pence per euro and
advanced 0.2 percent to $1.5478.  The number of people looking for work fell 4,000 to 2.51
million in the second quarter, today’s figures show.  To contact the reporter on this story:
